         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">3/1/96. ¶  ¶ Am greatly cheered by the kind sentiments, expressed in your letter, ¶  dear Mr Bradshaw, and never expected that you should aid the alpine exploration of New Guinea by substantial means ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">96.01.03</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Bradshaw</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Private hands.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">3/1/96.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Am greatly cheered by the kind sentiments, expressed in your letter,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found.</p>
               </note> dear Mr Bradshaw, and never expected that you should aid the alpine exploration of New Guinea by substantial means yourself. But I thought, that you might indicate some people, on whom fortune had lastingly smiled, who would <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">like</hi>
               </seg> to support the enterprise on the chance of some grand geographic feature being named in their honor. Mr Gunn<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bradshaw's cousin, Aeneas Gunn; see M to A. Gunn, 29 December 1895.</p>
               </note> perhaps is partly on this errand in Western Victoria. If so, I trust that he will wait also on the Manifolds and the Wilsons.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Owners of sheep stations in the Western District, Vic.</p>
               </note> If you know any particular Adress of Mr Wilson now, I would like to write to him.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With best reciprocation of your kind newyear's wishes your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferd von Mueller</p>
         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
